Some of the houses have signs hanging out front, advertising their trade or business. On the side of the road, a group of children play with a stick and hoop, their laughter and shouts echoing through the street. A few chickens peck at the dirt, occasionally darting out of the way of a passing cart or group of people. In the distance, you can see a small market square, where vendors sell goods ranging from fresh vegetables to handmade pottery. A few street performers entertain the crowd with juggling, tumbling, and music. As you continue down the street, you catch glimpses of people going about their daily business. A blacksmith works at his forge, a baker kneads dough in her shop, and a seamstress sews clothes for a customer. The town crier makes his rounds, announcing the latest news and events to the townspeople. Despite the crowded and bustling nature of the street, there is a sense of community and familiarity among the people.
